'''''Ahasveeruse uni''''' is a 2001 novel by [[Estonians|Estonian]] author [[Ene Mihkelson]]. The protagonist of the novel is a woman born in 1944, who during independence in the 1990s, looks through the [[Soviet era]] archives to find information about the fate of her parents after the [[World War II|Second World War]], in which they died in mysterious circumstances. The novel was selected by literary scholars, editors, writers and academics in a 2006 survey conducted to find the great novels published in Estonia in the post-occupation period.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://epl.delfi.ee/news/kultuur/taasiseseisvunud-eesti-parim-romaan-on-ahasveeruse-uni?id=51053462|title=Taasiseseisvunud Eesti parim romaan on "Ahasveeruse uni"|publisher=''[[Eesti Päevaleht]]''|date=23 August 2006|accessdate=1 April 2015|language=Estonian}}</ref>

