'''BPL''' is the call sign of the official long-wave [[time signal]] service of the [[People's Republic of China]], operated by the [[Chinese Academy of Sciences]], broadcasting on 100&nbsp;kHz from CAS's [[National Time Service Center]]<ref>{{Citation |url=http://english.ntsc.cas.cn |title=National Time Service Center}}</ref> in  [[Pucheng County, Shaanxi]] at {{Coord|34|56|54|N|109|32|34|E|type:landmark_region:CN-61|display=it}},<ref>{{Citation |url=ftp://ftp2.bipm.org/pub/tai/scale/TIMESIGNALS/timesignals.pdf |title=Time Signals |publisher=BIPM |page=78 |accessdate=2011-04-20}}</ref> roughly 70&nbsp;km northeast of [[Lintong District|Lintong]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.ntsc.cas.cn/rs/fs/200909/t20090917_39104.html|title=Facilities - National Time Service Center (NTSC), Chinese Academy of Sciences}}</ref> along with NTSC's short-wave time signal [[BPM (time service)|BPM]] on 2.5, 5.0, 10.0, and 15.0 [[Megahertz|MHz]].

BPL broadcasts [[LORAN-C]] compatible format signal from 5:30 to 13:30 UTC,<ref>{{cite web|title=长波授时 (Longwave time signal)|url=http://www.time.ac.cn/serve/BPL.htm|work=National Time Service Center, Chinese Academy of Sciences|publisher=National Time Service Center, Chinese Academy of Sciences|accessdate=16 March 2013}}</ref> using an 800&nbsp;kW transmitter covering a radius up to 3000&nbsp;km.<ref>{{cite web|title=科研成果 (Research achievements)|url=http://www.ntsc.cas.cn/kycg/|work=National Time Service Center, Chinese Academy of Sciences|publisher=National Time Service Center, Chinese Academy of Sciences|accessdate=16 March 2013}}</ref>

