{{Infobox prepared food | name = Finikia | image = Finikia at the 2011 Greek Festival.jpg | image_size = 300px | imagesize = | caption = | alternate_name = | country = [[Greece]] | region = | creator = | type = [[Cookie]] | served = | main_ingredient = [[Almond]]s, [[orange juice]], [[honey]], and grains | variations = | calories = | other = }} '''Finikia''' or '''Phinikia''' is a type of [[Ancient Greece|Greek]] cookie.<ref name=cook>{{cite web | url=http://allrecipes.com//Recipe/finikia/Detail.aspx | work=Allrecipes.com | title=Finikia | accessdate=2010-12-21}}</ref>
==Preparation== The cookie is made using flour, baking powder, orange juice, and oil. No dairy products are used. After baking in the oven, the finikia are rolled in a mixture of cinnamon, sugar and ground walnuts. Melomakarona, another type of Greek cookie dessert, is made with the same ingredients, but after baking, is dipped into a syrup mixture consisting of sugar, honey, water, orange zest, and cloves. Then it is rolled in the ground walnut, sugar and cinnamon mixture.<ref name=cook/>
