{{Infobox prepared food | name = Idrijski žlikrofi | image = Zlikrofi.jpg | image_size = 200px | imagesize = | caption = | alternate_name = | country = [[Slovenia]] | region = [[Idrija]] | creator = | type = [[Dumplings]] | served = | main_ingredient = [[Flour]], [[Egg (food)|egg]]s, [[potato]]es, [[lard]] | variations = | calories = | other = }}
'''Idrijski žlikrofi''' are traditional [[Slovenian cuisine|Slovenian]] dumplings that originate from [[Idrija]].<ref>{{cite book|title=Strategija razvoja gastronomije Slovenije|year=2006|publisher=Univerza v Mariboru|location=Maribor}}</ref> They are made from dough with potato filling and are often served either as a side dish to meat or on their own, in which case they are topped with breadcrumbs.<ref name="Adamlje1995">{{cite book|last=Adamlje|first=Slavko|title=Slovenska kuhinja|year=1995|publisher=Mladinska knjiga|location=Ljubljana|page=123}}</ref> The recipe dates back to the mid 19th century and remains one of the most popular Slovenian dishes.<ref>{{cite web|last=Prešeren|first=Polona|title=Idrijski žlikrofi - a true speciality of Idrija|url=http://www.slovenia.si/visit/cuisine/modern-culinary-trends/idrijski-zlikrofi-a-true-speciality-of-idrija/}}</ref> Žlikrofi were awarded a [[protected geographical status]] in 2010, the first Slovenian dish to do so.<ref>{{cite news|title=Idrijski žlikrofi tudi evropsko zaščiteni|url=http://www.rtvslo.si/gospodarstvo/idrijski-zlikrofi-tudi-evropsko-zasciteni/221382|accessdate=23 June 2013|date=15 January 2010}}</ref>
