'''Magicworld''' is a general entertainment channel produced for [[Dstv]] by [[MNET Series]].

==History==
When Mnet's Open Time Prime Time block was closed they sought a new service to keep viewership of the popular programs in the block up. To do this they would need to be affordable to all families in order to do this. [[Dstv]] wanted to launch a scaled down package for low income households for the cost of R19.00. The second half of open time was kept for this new pay TV package and also wanted to launch with a service called Mnet Lite. Up to the end of the Open Time block this new offer was heavily advertised on the pay TV [[Terrestrial channel]]. A lot of secrecy was around this new channel and when launched it was a combination of rerun and first run content from [[Channel O]] and the rest of the Mnet Channels. From 2200 to 1100 the channel would simulcast completely with [[Channel O]]. It was also  launched to promote South African movies but later evolved into a fullscale General Entertainment Channel. Its prime time also has reruns but also contains the [[United States|American]] [[reality show]] ''[[Starting Over (TV series)|Starting Over]]''. It still contains African produced movies during prime time.{{Citation needed|date=August 2011}}

==2009==
In 2009 the channel started simulcasting [[M-Net|Mnet]]'s New Youth Channel [[Vuzu's]] flagship program, V Entertainment. Whenever there is a major local reality program running it will broadcast on the channel like ''[[Idols (South Africa)|Idols]]'' in its entirety and later ''[[Big Brother Africa]]'''s weekly highlight show. When [[Dstv]] cut ''[[All Africa Poker]]'', they moved it content to be broadcast on Magicworld from 2230 to 0430 with [[Channel O]] picking up where they leave off all the way to 1100. It now also reruns popular [[Kenyan]] [[talk show]], ''[[The Patricia Show]]''.

==2015==
M-Net Family a general entertainment channel launched on channel 162 to replace the underperforming channel Magicworld and the only shows remaining on this new channel were ''[[The Wild (Drama Series)|The Wild]]'', ''[[The Talk (talk show)|The Talk]]'' and the kids block Koowe later in 2016 the channel had a program reshuffle leaving only ''The Talk'' as the only current program from the defunct Magicworld. In 2017, M-Net Family was discontinued due to low ratings and programs from M-Net Family moved to [[Vuzu]].

