{{Infobox rockunit | name = Calizas y margas de Xert Formation | image = | caption = | type = [[Geological formation]] | age = [[Cretaceous|Cretaceous Period]] | prilithology = | otherlithology = | namedfor = | namedby = | region = | country =[[Spain]] | coordinates = | unitof = | subunits = | underlies = | overlies = | thickness = | extent = | area = | map = | map_caption = }}
The '''Calizas y margas de Xert Formation''' or '''Xert Formation''' is a [[Cretaceous]] period [[geologic formation]] in [[Spain]].
[[Mesozoic Era]] [[dinosaur]] remains are among the fossils that have been recovered from the formation, although none have yet been referred to a specific [[genus]].<ref name="dinosaurdistribution">Weishampel, et al. (2004). "Dinosaur distribution." Pp. 517-607.</ref>
